IBE — Maps, 1-on-1 Chat, Squad Management, & Feed Fixes
This implementation plan covers major platform upgrades, including replacing the lobby-based group chat with a robust 1-on-1 Direct Messaging system, adding free interactive Leaflet maps, and resolving broken squad management features.
________________________________________
Proposed Changes
1. Interactive Maps (Leaflet + OpenStreetMap)
We will use Leaflet with OpenStreetMap to provide a completely free, highly capable map experience without needing Google API keys or billing accounts.
•	MapPicker.jsx: A reusable component offering an interactive map, draggable marker, and a search bar powered by Nominatim (OpenStreetMap's geocoder). It reverse-geocodes clicked points to extract address, city, and country, and includes a "📍 Use My Location" feature.
•	MapEmbed.jsx: A read-only map component for displaying locations on detail pages.
•	Integration:
•	Replace raw lat/lng number inputs on LobbyCreate.jsx and VenueApply.jsx with the MapPicker.
•	Add MapEmbed to LobbyDetail.jsx and VenueProfile.jsx to visually show the location.
2. Location-Aware Feed
•	Backend (Lobby model): Add city and country fields to the location sub-document and index them for fast querying.
•	Backend (Lobby Controller): Update getLobbies to accept city and country params alongside the existing geospatial queries.
•	Frontend (Feed.jsx):
•	Add a "📍 Near Me" button that requests browser geolocation and passes lng and lat to dynamically sort the feed by distance.
•	Add native dropdowns for City and Country filtering.
•	Include a distance radius selector (10km, 25km, 50km).
3. 1-on-1 Direct Messaging (Person-to-Person Chat)
Replaces the previous Lobby-based group chat concept.
•	Backend Schema (Message.js): Restructure the schema to facilitate direct messaging:
•	Remove lobbyId.
•	Add senderId and receiverId.
•	Backend Routes & Controllers:
•	GET /messages/inbox → Fetch a list of active conversations (grouped by user with latest message).
•	GET /messages/:userId → Fetch the message history with a specific user.
•	POST /messages/:userId → Send a DM to a user.
•	Socket.io Handlers: Update events to use send_direct_message and route it directly to user:{receiverId} instead of lobby rooms.
•	Frontend (Messages.jsx): Create a new dedicated global Inbox page accessible from the Navbar.
•	Left pane: List of recent conversations.
•	Right pane: Active chat history with the selected user.
•	Integrations: Delete the "Chat" tab from LobbyDetail.jsx. Instead, add a "Message Organizer" button that redirects the user to the global /messages page with that user pre-selected.
4. Squad Routing & Member Management
•	Routing Fix: SquadCreate and VenueApply pages currently exist in the codebase but are missing from App.jsx. We will add their routes.
•	Backend (squad.controller.js): Add a new removeMember endpoint allowing captains to kick players.
•	Frontend (SquadProfile.jsx):
•	Add an "Add Member" interface for the captain to manually add players by email or username search.
•	Add "Remove" buttons next to players in the roster for the captain.
•	Add a "Leave Squad" button for non-captain members.
5. Remove W/L/D Stats from Squads
•	Currently, squads show Wins/Losses on their cards and profiles. Per requirements, we will remove this UI completely from SquadProfile.jsx and SquadDiscovery.jsx.
6. Organizer Contact Number Visibility
•	LobbyDetail.jsx: Ensure the organizer's WhatsApp and Email are clearly visible on the lobby detail sidebar for all logged-in users, instead of just confirmed players.
•	LobbyCard.jsx: Display the WhatsApp number directly on the live feed cards.
•	Profile.jsx: Show the user's WhatsApp number on their public profile view.
